clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: For the lowering of intraocular pressure in patients with open angle glaucoma or ocular hypertension who are intolerant of other intraocular pressure lowering medications or insufficiently responsive failed to achieve target IOP determined after multiple measurements over time to another intraocular pressure lowering medication

contraindications.disease: LD50 in rats 1g Kg subcutaneous 93500 µg Kg IV
contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Unoprostone will begin to reduce IOP 30 minutes after ocular instillation
